juniHdlcAgent.name: juniHdlcAgent

revisions.description: Added support for HDLC interface idle character.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
The initial release of this management information module.

juniHdlcAgent.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@Juniper.net
juniHdlcAgent.description: The agent capabilities definitions for the HDLC component of the SNMP agent in the Juniper E-series family of products.

juniHdlcAgentV1.name: juniHdlcAgentV1
juniHdlcAgentV1.productrelease:
Version 1 of the HDLC component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.  This version
        of the HDLC component was supported in JUNOSe 1.0 system releases.
juniHdlcAgentV1.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the HDLC application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when juniHdlcIfDataPolarity was added.

juniHdlcAgentV2.name: juniHdlcAgentV2
juniHdlcAgentV2.productrelease:
Version 2 of the HDLC component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.  This version
        of the HDLC component was supported in JUNOSe 1.1 thru 3.0 system
        releases.
juniHdlcAgentV2.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the HDLC application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when more objects were added.

juniHdlcAgentV3.name: juniHdlcAgentV3
juniHdlcAgentV3.productrelease:
Version 3 of the HDLC component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.  This version
        of the HDLC component is supported in JUNOSe 3.1 through 5.0 system
        releases.
juniHdlcAgentV3.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the HDLC application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when HDLC interface idle character support was added.

juniHdlcAgentV4.name: juniHdlcAgentV4
juniHdlcAgentV4.productrelease:
Version 3 of the HDLC component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.  This version
        of the HDLC component is supported in JUNOSe 5.1 and subsequent system
        releases.
juniHdlcAgentV4.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the HDLC application in JUNOSe.
